         Method Overloading                                     Method Overriding

Provides functionality to reuse a method             Used to override a behavior which the
name with different parameters.                      class has inherited from the parent
                                                     class.

Usually in a single class but may also               Always in two classes that have a
be used in a child class.                            child-parent or IS-A relationship.

Must have different parameters.                      Must have the same parameters and
                                                     same name.

May have different return types.                     Must have the same return type or
                                                     covariant return type (child class).

May have different access                            Must NOT have a lower modifier but
modifiers(private,protected, public).                may have a higher modifier.

May throw different exceptions.                      Must NOT throw a new or broader
                                                     checked exception